==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[Μίνως]]''' (''Minos''), the king of [[Crete]].

===Adjective===
#Of or related to the Minoan civilization that developed in [[Crete]] from the [[neolithic]] period to the [[stone age]] (about 3000-1050 BCE).
#Of or relating to the writing systems ([[Linear A]] and [[Linear B]]) used in Crete and later in mainland Greece.

===Noun===
#A Cretan who belonged to the Minoan civilization. 

===Translations===
*Greek: [[Μινωικός]] (''Minoikos'')

